### 3. Credit Rating

A County Court Judgment (CCJ) will seriously damage your credit rating, making it difficult to:
- Rent another property
- Obtain credit or loans
- Get a mortgage
- Pass employment checks

### 4. Eviction

If the court grants possession, you will be evicted. You may be made homeless and the local council may decide you made yourself intentionally homeless, meaning they will not have a duty to rehouse you.

### 5. Future References

You will find it very difficult to rent another property with an eviction and CCJ on your record.

